cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on graph-to-sequence learning, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep learning architecture, which involves graph convolutional networks (GCNs), a popular technique in computer vision (CV) and graph-based ML. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its model on AMR-to-text generation, which involves semantic parsing and text generation, and syntax-based neural machine translation, which involves syntactic parsing and machine translation. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
